The paper focuses on indoor localization using acoustic properties of rooms, which falls under the category of signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of statistical analysis and algorithms for feature extraction, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for energy management in buildings, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
